HEADWORD: fine-looking
<hw>fine-looking</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>pleasing in appearance
especially by reason of conformity to ideals of form and proportion;
<as>as, a <ex>fine-looking</ex> woman</as>.</def>[Narrower terms:
<stype>beautiful (vs. ugly) </stype>]⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> good-looking, better-looking, handsome,
well-favored, well-favoured.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

